iar of Guinevere<br>Sonnie<br>6 Armsman of Guinivere <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/urassaths.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rassaths</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 727<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/28/01 7:08:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://rass7th.homestead.com/Files/rassface3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Its odd...</span><hr size=1> With every new game I think that large populations will certainly have played online games before and have some clue of etiquette.  I'm always wrong.<br><br>I've had sooooo many people just /invite me to their groups without asking.<br><br>I've had people say &quot;how rich are you?&quot;.<br><br>Then again, I've seen multiple groups working an 8 spawn camp with no pull steals.  I was running to do a quest yesterday and ressed two people who fell just as I approached, both of whom were totally amazed and happy. <p><img src="http://rass7th.homestead.com/Files/rassig.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/utrueheart78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trueheart78</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/EQ/dance.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 458<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/29/01 7:02:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/EQ/dancinghobbes.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Its odd...</span><hr size=1> i've met my share of exp leechers, that's for sure.<br><br>When you solo in tomb of mithra, it's understandable to have someone grab an extra off you if 2 approach, and you know you can handle it.  I don't mind.<br><br>But when some orange con prick starts doing his moves on something that you have in the bag np, you start get a lil pissy.  Especially when you see the whole guild pulling that crap later the same night, as a whole.<br><br>Oh, btw, consider any Of swords and Sorrow members blacklisted, at least for me and likely Gyan also.  Had a run in with them, not pretty.<br><br>Ah well, just a heads up. leechers are everywhere, just gotta lay down the law, &quot;Excuse me sir/madam, but I am perfectly fit to handle these encounters, if you would so please refrain from aiding enemies I have engaged or I shall have to report you to the local authorities.&quot; sure it doesnt make much sense but once you tell someone you're gonna report em for bein an ass, they tend to lay off abit. <p><DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/starspangled.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uevilnight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EvilNight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 558<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/30/01 5:50:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Its odd...</span><hr size=1> Tip for dealing with leechers...<br><br>Do your best not to really hurt the MoB, but appear to be fighting it. Carry a really shitty weapon with you for just this occasion. As soon as they cast something on the MoB, or heal you, guess who it's going to go after? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If you have Friar's Redress, just nail the MoB with that once or twice and it'll be all over the leecher.<br><br>Get them killed that way a couple of times and they won't be leeching off of you anymore... <p>Raviel Darkfyre<BR>55th Master of the Whistling Fist<BR><b>Insidious Blood</b><BR><BR>Arcus Stoneheart<BR>17th Fanatic of the Defenders of Albion<BR><b>The Brotherhood</b><BR><BR>Ravian Skyfire<BR>8th Pyromancer of the Lethantis Association<BR><b>The Brotherhood</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/utrueheart78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trueheart78</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/EQ/dance.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/30/01 6:21:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/EQ/dancinghobbes.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Its odd...</span><hr size=1> Works great for people that you know cant take the mob solo or would have a hard time, but for someone that's orange to ya, just doesn't work that way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.siscom.net/~blacklion/starspangled.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=130.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showNextMessage?topic